item.title: Total Lunar Eclipse 21 Dec 2010
item.description:
Total Lunar Eclipse 21 Dec 2010
Shot from my backyard using an Olympus SP-565 Ultra Zoom. Clips begin just prior to totality and conclude while the moon is in totality. It is a bit shaky as I was zoomed in at max (20 X Optical) and holding the camera in my hand. However, I think you still get a great idea of how 3D the moon looks when it is not in direct sunlight which causes it to look flat normally. An eclipse definitely gives the moon depth and texture. The clips were edited together and graphics added using Windows Live Movie Maker 2011. Enjoy. Richard Hay http://WindowsObserver.com Location: Jacksonville, Florida
